{"id":"ev_757e2da5a36047ba","runId":"run_251","type":"delegation","at":1782499704572,"data":{"workItemId":"wi_6645254da3ee44db","atom":1,"task":"Build a REAL-PROCESS integration test that drives the runnerless path end-to-end through the REAL `runRun` — hardening item 1, the only remaining archive blocker.\n\nWHY THIS MATTERS: every existing proof of the runnerless path injects a fake runner (`runRunImpl` substituted in `runStandalone`, see packages/cli/tests/run-independent.test.ts). So the live wiring between `runStandalone` and a real `runRun` on the independent path has NEVER actually executed — it is only exercised structurally. This atom closes that gap.\n\nNON-NEGOTIABLE CONSTRAINT — do NOT inject the runner. `runRunImpl` must NOT be substituted; the test must invoke the REAL `runRun` (packages/core/src/runner/runner.ts) through the real `runStandalone` (packages/cli/src/run.ts). If you find yourself passing a fake `runRunImpl`, you have missed the point of this atom. You MAY stub only the AGENT layer (the codex/claude CLI adapters and/or the cmux session host) at the lowest layer available, so the orchestration loop runs deterministically without real LLMs or terminals — but the runner orchestration, the store, the scratch runsRoot, and the directive/verify file handoff must all be REAL.\n\nFIRST, INVESTIGATE (read before changing): how `runRun` resolves and invokes agents via `RunnerDeps` (`getAdapter`, `sessionHost`, `io`), and how the existing core test `packages/core/tests/runner-direct.test.ts` already drives a real `runRun` daemon-free — reuse its agent-stubbing approach. Determine the lowest seam where you can substitute scripted agents WITHOUT touching `runRunImpl`. If a tiny, behavior-preserving seam in `runStandalone` is needed to inject fake adapters/session-host at the deps level (NOT the runner), keep it minimal and guarded so production behavior is unchanged.\n\nWHAT THE TEST MUST DO:\n1. Run with NO daemon (probe naturally not-alive, or daemon-down) — the daemon-up guard from atom 0 must pass cleanly.\n2. Drive a scripted agent sequence (Oscar delegate → Bob build → Oscar verify pass → complete) through the REAL runRun loop, over the REAL directive/verify file handoff in the scratch/real runsRoot.\n3. Cover BOTH the non-destructive (live runsRoot/store) case AND the `destructive` isolated-scratch case (live store untouched, scratch store copied + used).\n\nASSERTIONS (the seams the disposition flagged as most likely to break first):\n- The run reaches completion via the real runRun (e.g. RunResult shows completed and the run record.md exists on disk).\n- The scratch/real `runsRoot` ↔ directive/verify file handoff actually occurred (directive-*.json / verify-*.json were written and consumed at the real runsRoot path used by runStandalone — not a mock path).\n- The REAL SQLite store was opened via `openRunStore` and the single-writer lock behaved correctly on the real path (a real DB file exists at the resolved dbPath; for the destructive case it is the scratch copy and `local/cocoder.db` is untouched).\n- `runRunImpl` was NOT injected (assert/structure the test so the real runRun is what executed).\n\nEXIT CRITERION: `pnpm --filter @cocoder/cli exec tsc --noEmit` exits 0, the full `@cocoder/cli` test suite passes (not just the new test — this change may touch shared wiring), and the new integration test passes. Report the exact commands and their output, and confirm in your summary that the real runRun (not a fake) executed.\n\nWRITE SCOPE: packages/cli/tests/** and packages/core/tests/** (test + minimal shared test harness/fixtures), plus a MINIMAL behavior-preserving deps-injection seam in packages/cli/src/run.ts ONLY if required to inject fake adapters/session-host without injecting runRunImpl. Do not change runner orchestration logic, the commit spine, or store code."}}
